(link-reveal: "chlorophyll")[
	&nbsp ˈklôrəˌfil
	&nbsp <i>noun</i>
	&nbsp a green pigment, present in all green plants and in cyanobacteria, responsible for the absorption of light to provide energy for photosynthesis.
	&nbsp If only humans could produce chlorophyll, she'd never have to move again.
]
(link-reveal: "phlegmatic")[
	&nbsp fleɡˈmadik
